	   <tr><td colspan=2>'Good' is a subjective term - it depends whether you want all tha advantages of max/min'ing a character, or whether you'd like to role-play that character a bit.<br><br>Have a look at the race descriptions and see which one takes your fancy, don't be bound by statistics, the world of Norrath is supposed to be a diverse and fun place! As you grow in power, you'll find items that will make up for any early deficiency in stats.<br><br>As far as bonus points go, put as many as you can into WIS - this determines how much mana you get, so do give yourself the best start possible there.<br>&nbsp;<br>Kelanthor<br>Wood Elf Druid of the 41st Circle<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=212672" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=212672</a></td></tr>
