	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Mar 7th 4:41 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.60]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Your post title befuddles me as well ;) but,<br><br>lets see at level 7<br><br>Hunting the orc hill in a group is a good start, i'd save the belts maybe and get yourself some armor and exp for turning them in at kaladim if you have no armor yet.<br><br>you can always try to sell the belts for a pp each or whatever the going price is on your server.<br><br>Don't for get, loot all rusty items and cloth items, sell them, it adds up, especially if you are a brand new player.<br><br>Spells at level 5 you should have are the invoke lightning (can't remember its been like 41 levels since i used it last), snare definetly, and healing spell and any nuke you have.<br>Level 9 you get a nicer direct damage and light heal. At lvl 8 you get meditate to regain mana faster.<br><br>If you don't like gfay, take a ride on over to freeport and hunt in East Commons or Northern Ro desert. Save all kinds of pelts and silks there, sell them for like 10pp or 20pp a stack depending on quality to aspiring tailors.<br><br>If you can manage to save like 6 pp, get two silver jasper rings from an enchanter (make sure its the ones that add wisdom).<br>Also, look for split paw hide gloves for 5pp for a quick 2 wis 3 dex pair of gloves.<br>Ulthork hide arms may be another good choice, most people sell them to vendors, so offer like 5 or 10 pp to the person for them.<br><br>Once you get higher level, get into a group in crushbone itself and sell the nice bronze weapons to vendors and crushbone shoulderpads to players for 3pp each.<br>Or you can go try to find willowisps at like level 13(beware, you need a magic weapon to hit them or hit them with magic spells, so maybe a velium scimitar or warhammer would be in order, see if anyone is selling their velium to a vendor and ask if you can give them 5pp for it rather then them selling it for 4pp to a vendor). Willowisps drop lighstones and greater light stones which sell for 8pp to a vendor and 3pp to a vendor respectively, or maybe a few people would want to buy a greater light stone.<br><br>That should get you going, ask a local druid in game what they suggest if you forget or need real time advice.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
