	   <tr><td colspan=2>If you are in a group, NOBODY in the group should have to ask for your buffs or heals. They certainly shouldn't have to beg or say please. If a group member says SOW, or Heal, it is just their way of casually reminding you that you aren't doing your job. My main is a cleric, and if I ever screw up so badly that someone in my group has to ASK for a heal, I would apologize. I also never expect them to have to say please for buffs, because its my job to provide them. Thats my role in the group. I don't have to ask the warrior to hit the mobs, and I'd better not have to ask him to taunt.&nbsp;&nbsp;When I need a peel, I usually try to throw in a plz, but if I don't the warriors/melees never seem to get upset. Why, because peeling is part of their group role. Now, if it is something uncommon, like getting zinged because they have low stamina, or a heavy weapon, they need to ask, because I usually don't keep it memmed, but they don't need to say please. again, its part of my job.<br><br>The druid's role in a group should always include: sow(for everyone if mana permits, at least for puller), buffs (which ones depends on who's also buffing the group), Damage shield (for Main assist, and anyone else who gets aggro), Heals (depending on whether there is a cleric in the group), evacs (for those ugly overpulls, unless the wizzy is evacing), Nukes (as needed, and as mana permits, this isn't really the druid's main role). Clearly, some of these roles can be taken over by other group members, depending on group composition, but you should expect to be doing at least some of these, and your group members should not have to ask for these things to be done.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
