	   <tr><td colspan=2>Are Druids wanted later/are Rangers wanted later.<br>Answers Yes and Yes... IF you know how to play. First off. Ranger: if your the whirling Dervish of death with your two epics, and fly into mobs fist a swinging.. your probly going to die, get others killed and not get in groups. However: if you set back, let the MA get the agro hold it then attack you can do a crap load of damage and never get agro. you dont have to get healed as much and there for clerics arnt alway oom (cause face it you mostly have lower ac then warriors the same lvl) also a good tactic is to fight then back off for a min to let the MA get the agro back.<br>Druid: yep you are wanted also. long as you know your role, mostly at high lvls you will be back up healer and snarer. Also in group situations you could possibly Ds (when mage not around) and buff. Also the Ro's line of spells have opened up lots of Debuffing avenues that we didnt have before. But you have to be careful MOBS HATE THESE.<br>Basicly you can get groups if you know how to play and are friendly. Also being in a guild helps lots. <br><br>&nbsp;<br>Regnon Plainswalker Lvl 55 Druid of NIHIL Bertox<br>What the heck was that?.....darn bixie stinger</td></tr>
