	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Feb 27th 9:53 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.30]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Remember the likelihood of higher level mobs resisting your snares! If your first snare doesn't take and you don't have sow, you're looking at a quick death. This tactic would probably work better in a partnership with a melee type to deal out damage while you snare and fear the pumas.<br><br>Don't overlook the fear animal line of spells that a druid has: a free invitation to beat up their behinds while you're taking no damage. Once again, this spell works great in a partnership with a melee type to do the damage while you med or cast. You'll get Panic Animal at level 1 (10 mana) to start off your career nice and easy!<br><br>Let me also put a word in for the Druid DoT/debuff line of spells that begins with Flame Lick. As long as you have a fire beetle eye in your inventory you can cast Flame Lick and start using this as a great way to soften up the mobs.<br><br>Finally, don't waste your time (and ours) begging. A helpful, hardworking newbie can earn decent plat (enough to buy the valuable low level spells) doing some of the newbie quests, killing mobs and accumulating stacks of items such as bonechips (for Kaladim quest or for sale to other player). You'll find it quicker levelling than hanging around your server's auction zone, begging for plat!<br>&nbsp;<br>-- Ancarett, who lives at <a href="http://ancarett.com" target=_new>http://ancarett.com</a></td></tr>
