	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101483415012438><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=101483415012438>RE: newbie help</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=101483415012438#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=133423><span id=Scholar>darkparable</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>47 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Feb 27th 1:23 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I too played a new druid in GFay. I would agree with some of the other posters. Stay away from orc pawns as they will aggro on you and try to kill you quickly. There are a lot of druids in GFay. Therefore I would recommend exclusively killing bats. After killing one heal yourself up to full hitpoints and kill the next bat. Make sure you have Skin of Wood cast on yourself as you need every advantage you can get right now. The game gets a lot easier at second level and if you're a little careful your first four levels should fly by. The reason to kill bats is there is a lot of call in GFay for batwings (they are a component in the levitate spell). On my server the typical rate for a stack of 20 bw is 3pp. Usually higher level characters will also cast buffs on you that will allow you to survive easier. If you see a skeleton carrying a weapon once you're level two or three hunt them--only hunt them at first if they are alone if there are two or more skeletons togethr they will team up on you. There are quests for the weapons, but in general they can be sold to merchants for food money and spell money...though if you die before level four your food is replenished.<br><br>Don't give up...It gets easier and more fun.<br><br>Averill<br>12th lvl Druid<br>Morell-Thule<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Feb 27 13:23:48 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
