	   <tr><td colspan=2>When i first started playing, I tried a woodelf ranger.&nbsp;&nbsp;I had this very same problem.  Eventually some of my friends helped me out and informed me that Gfay (Greater Faydark/kelethin) is one of the hardest starting zones for someone that is absolutely new to the game(like it sounds you are).I would suggest starting a char in freeport, kaladim, or halas in order to get used to the interface and learn how to con your targets first and what to fight and what not to fight.  Then look at what class/race you really want to play and then learn to play it well.  <br><br>Here is a website that can help you learn some of the race/class combo setups and starting areas/strategies:<br>    <a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/" target=_new>http://eq.castersrealm.com/</a><br><br>And here is a link that can help with maps of most of the zones that you will be able to get to anytime soon:<br>    <a href="http://www.eqatlas.com/" target=_new>http://www.eqatlas.com/</a><br><br>Hope that this helps.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
